column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: -Open water conditions. Ice hanging and hung up on boulders on RHB but no (minimal) affect on flow.
column14: -RiverPro measurement from moving boat about 150m upstream of gauge. -Large shift expected. Previous was .220 and they have been steadily growing over past few years. -Turned off first two transects as the edge didnt capture the RHB correctly. underestimated think the edge was going to get shallower quicker. -RHB captures the input of the small stream on the RHB upstream of the gauge. ADCP temp drops as it crosses into the different colored water from the creek. -@ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken about 30m downstream of gauge. Same spot as last few years and near where sensor deployed. -Second rod left in water to track stage during measurement as sensor freshly deployed -OTT offset 1.515. Could not get deeper. ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: -0.004 Surge: 0.003  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.
GC: 0.000 HG: 1.141 HG2: 0.677 Surge: 0.005  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13:
-Clear of ice, No debris observed running or snagged in river.
-Rock outcrop exposed in front of gauge
column14: -M9 in trimaran from manned boat ~200m upstream. -MGH taken from time-weighted between cuts due to blocks just being deployed and OTT at least showing signs of settling. -Large shift value is in line with last few measurements. Supports control change. -Large edge estimates as large shallow shores. Q value is minimal compared to to total. -gravel bar exposed about 40m upstream of LHB -@ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken downstream ~50m, where lines enter water. Roughly in line with fallen tree overhanging bank. -Offsets: OTT1.403, Bubbler 1.888 ADCP by Moving Boat
GC: 0.000 HG2: 0.679 Surge: 0.005  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.
GC: 0.000 HG: 2.411 HG2: 2.097 Surge: 0.005  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: Open water conditions.  No visible changes to control as it is channel control.  No big debris piles or debris of any kind.
column14: -Measured approx 150m downstream from gauge. -MBT closed in upstream direction. Did not repeat due to time constraints. MB unlikely.  Calculated MGH 3 different ways with HG, HG2 and DWL's no significant difference.  Used HG2 (OTT submerisble) for MGH as it is the average of both MGH readings. -old bubbler sub 1.801 new 1.608.  HG bubbler HG2 submersible.  Reset bubbler only, thought it was the HG2 and sub was HG.  ADCP by Moving Boat
GC: 0.000 HG: 2.411 HG2: 2.094 Surge: 0.005  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Smokey , No Precipitation , Calm Wind
column13: Unable to determine status of control visually.  Need measurement to confirm status of control.
column14: Used RiverPro from manned boat.  Measured approx 80m upstream.  Large LHB estimate as shallow and rocky.  No GPS so used loop test, not ideal so did two to make sure. Bubb offset 2.36, sub offset 1.801, Planned to deploy submersible to try and avoid silting conditions.  Found gas line pulled downstream with block torn off and line floating in the water.  No chance for an SRC.  Used two dwl as the MGH as the line were deployed right before mmnt.  Took a second DWL RP2 approx 20m downstream of initial DWL to see if there is a large change in slope.  3.076m DWL and secondary DWL 3.067m  Does not appear to be a significant change. ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Light Wind
column13: Open water conditions.  Some small ice pans on shore not particulary high on the banks.
column14: Attempted to use ARC boat for discharge mmnt.  Rudders on ARC boat would not operate.  Tried troubleshooting with no success.  Used a rope and tied the boat to the tethered boat pole.  Used motor on site to do a tethered boat from manned boat mmnt.  -No HG reading at time of DWL as line was being replaced. Cut was checked after block reset and no change although there was a 10mm surge. -drop in stage during visit visually observed on rod left in water, was just out of water on departure (about 20mm drop) ADCP by Moving Boat
Reset (RS)
downstream of bedrock
HG: 2.698 SRC: 0.295 Reset (RS)
HG: 2.683 SRC: 0.818 Reset (RS)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , Light Rain , Calm Wind
column13: Recent evidence of high waater event. Trees hung up on downstream gravel bar now gone. Boulders have recently been moved and caught existing line.
column14: Measured ~200m u/s just below creek input on RHB External GPS failed to communicate. Not used. Large shift and error values in line with previious measurements since extreme high water event several years ago  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of 0.818 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 2.683 Brass Cap in bedrock below cut bank appears to be gone now. ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column14: -upstream where small stream enter RHB -MBT done over mainflow to limit to 70m loop -Line found seperated at union near tree at cutbank - block end not recovered -new line attached and block deployed just below standing waves section -new OD 1.864 / offset 1.476 ADCP by Moving Boat
Reset (RS)

Subsectioned transect 003.  Measured downstream of gauge.  Almost too shallow for the RRAY.  Consider using a different instrument if measuring at this stage again.  Mmnt section kind of turbulent.  Not likely a streampro would fair very well here.  Have to try it or a RPRO or a 1200.  QREV discharge of 208 was used. Sources:Manual
